The naive Bayes classifier is used to solve a two-class classification problem with class-labels $y_{1}, y_{2}$. Suppose the prior probabilities are $P\left(y_{1}\right)=\dfrac{1}{3}$ and $P\left(y_{2}\right)=\dfrac{2}{3}$. Assuming a discrete feature space with
\[
P\left(x \mid y_{1}\right)=\dfrac{3}{4} \quad \text { and } \quad P\left(x \mid y_{2}\right)=\dfrac{1}{4}
\]
for a specific feature vector $x$. The probability of misclassifying $x$ is ____________ (Round off to two decimal places)
